Sentencas: In the present study, the results of the numerical implementation of a mathematical model of a planar anode-supported SOFC are reported.
Titulo: Modeling Carbon Monoxide Direct Oxidation in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In particular, model results are validated and discussed when the fuel is a mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide, focusing on the importance of simulating direct oxidation of carbon monoxide.
Titulo: Modeling Carbon Monoxide Direct Oxidation in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The mathematical model is solved in a 3D environment and the key issue is the validation comparing with experimental data, which is made in different operating conditions to establish the reliability of the presented model.
Titulo: Modeling Carbon Monoxide Direct Oxidation in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results show the importance of simulating direct oxidation of carbon monoxide and its effect on the fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Modeling Carbon Monoxide Direct Oxidation in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
